      "side": 1,
      "message": "We should probably have a comment somewhere explaining what is going on. Something like:\n\n// All the opsTasks generated by an SDC along with the SDC\u0027s RTP share a reffed\n// pointer to an SkArenas object. Whenever a opsTask is destroyed it nulls out\n// matching RTP\u0027s arena pointer. This guarantees the use/lifetime of the arenas \n// object matches a flush boundary.\n// In the usual case, everything is flushed together so all the opsTask get \n// executed and deleted. Removing the ref on the RTP so the arenas object gets\n// deleted.\n// In the partial flush case we could end up in a situation where some opsTasks\n// from and unflushed RTP get pulled into the flush. In this case, when the\n// extra opsTasks are flushed and destroyed they will clear the ref in the\n// RTP. In this case there can be some lingering opsTasks that still ref their\n// floating arenas object. It will, presumably, get deleted during a later flush\n// and, if more ops are targeted at the RTP it will create a new arenas object\n// to hold with the new opsTasks.",
      "revId": "1f6ff9d3d10109a3939b14f3a22d8c46eda13470",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
